data.title: Dolly Parton, Herschend Enterprises jointly acquire downtown Nashville property
data.meta_description: The Dollywood Company confirmed its acquisition of 211 Commerce Street in downtown Nashville to FOX 17 News.
data.text:
Does Tennessee icon Dolly Parton have something special in the works for Nashville?

The Dollywood Company confirmed to FOX 17 News it has acquired 211 Commerce Street in downtown Nashville.

The company says the acquisition is a joint venture between Herschend Enterprises and Dolly Parton.

“Since the pandemic, commercial real estate is becoming an opportunity,” said Dolly. “I strongly believe in the future of Nashville and feel this is a great investment.”

According to real estate company CBRE, 211 Commerce Street sold for $75 million. The company says the property is occupied by an 11-story tower built in 2000 that is currently home to office, retail and restaurant space.

CBRE reports the seller recently made $16 million improvements to the property, including a new conference center, fitness center, as well as renovations to the lobby, indoor/outdoor tenant lounge, elevators, outdoor plaza and exterior.

The Dollywood Company says terms of the sale will not be disclosed and plans for the future of 211 Commerce will be shared as they materialize.
